                        <seg type="script">Poor</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS00000">Za-Dǝngǝl</persName>Za-Dǝngǝl is the scribe of the text in quires IV-VI, mentioned in the supplication formula, <locus target="42r">42r</locus>. He is the same scribe who is attested in Ms. MR-040 and some other Mss. (QSM-005, MY-019, AQG-002, AGM-001). The hand of quires I-III is somewhat similar to that of MR-024.<date>19th cent.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donors and scribes; incipits of the texts and their subsections; elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation signs; Additio 1.</seg>
                     </handNote>
